reviews.review: Great movie! JJ did so much damage control for the last movie! Very proud to call this the final chapter of the Skywalker saga.

Great film. Filled with action, decent mix of nostalgia (too much fan service at times) but absolutely wrapped up the story well and Abrams did well utilizing Carrie Fisher and still made her an integral piece to the plot
Easily the best of the new trilogy.
Ignore the haters.  Its a great movie. Go see it and make your own decision.
Enjoyable but it does feel like two movies crammed into one
Some questions that need to be answered on some parts of the movie.  Show start but overall very good pulling story lines together.

The critics are hyper negative because it suits there business and generates clicks. Of course it has flaws and awkward moments, but evaluated on its own it has an intriguing plot, adds depth to understanding of the sith, and fleshes our both Rey and Kylo Ren's story satisfyingly.
Given where this movie had to pick up the pieces and cram in enough exposition while racing to the finish, The Rise of Skywalker is was a fitting end and should leave a warm spot in fans' bellies.

SPOILERS: JJ Abrams destroyed the Skywalker legacy in one disorganized, rushed, and quite frankly insulting mess. It was Game of Thrones Season 8 all over again. There was no character development and the writing was atrocious. This movie should have been called The Rise of Palpatine instead, because it was a Skywalker genocide to prop up a character given a Palpatine ancestry for pure shock value, which did not make any sense in the story as a whole. Rey taking the Skywalker name at the conclusion of the Star Wars saga was a slap in the face to longtime fans who entered theaters wanting to see the Skywalkers restored to their rightful place in a story that has lasted generations. 

This review is based solely on the story being told and is in no way reflective of the performance of the actors and crew who poured so much of their time and talent into this movie. They were the only saving grace The Rise of Skywalker had.
I loved this movie, it's everything I wanted and more.
